      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's an interesting way to put it. But some people would argue that nationalism is basically the root cause of most wars and xenophobia in history. If it's so \"vital\" for stability, how do you reconcile that with the fact that it often leads to \"us vs them\" mentalities that cause actual violence and oppression? Doesn't it inherently create conflict?",
