      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear what you saying about \"channeling it positively,\" but that feels like a pretty optimistic way to look at it. if we look at modern politics, it seems like nationalism is almost always being used to exclude people or push certain agendas. isn't it more realistic to say that nationalism is more of a threat to a peaceful, interconnected world than a tool for \"unity\"?",
